<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,788,1355]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,824,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The members of this genus can be recognized from all genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" box="[1039,1160,824,850]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Zodariinae">Zodariinae</taxonomicName>
occurring east of 
<collectingCountry box="[1356,1436,824,850]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Turkey</collectingCountry>
by having only six eyes (although rarely vestiges of AME are present, see 
<figureCitation box="[1006,1093,860,887]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1846,1870]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,348,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[151,1436,345,1822]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus of Trygetus gromovi Marusik, 2011 (A–D), T. susianus Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021 (E), T. cyrus sp. n. (F) and T. nakhchivanicus sp. n. (G, H). A, F female, dorsal; B same, lateral; C female’s abdomen and posterior part of cephalothorax, ventral; D female’s cephalothorax, anterior; E, H male, dorsal; G same, ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683485/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
), and the presence of a dorsal scutum in males (except for 
<taxonomicName authority="O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1872" box="[480,936,896,923]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Palaestina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[480,600,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Palaestina</emphasis>
O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872
</taxonomicName>
and some species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walckenaer, 1826" authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1826" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1290,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Zodarion</emphasis>
Walckenaer, 1826
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,788,1355]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,968,994]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Comments.</emphasis>
Currently eight species are considered in the genus, distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1176,969,995]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(one species) and from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1005,1031]" name="Egypt" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Egypt</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[253,411,1004,1030]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. Three of the easternmost species are known only from females, while the westernmost one is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[417,515,1040,1066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">holotype</typeStatus>
male. Considering the shape of the epigynes, species occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1255,1381,1040,1066]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1391,1436,1041,1067]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[197,352,1076,1102]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
seem to be misplaced, albeit being similar in habitus to those known from Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1258,1320,1076,1102]" name="Israel" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(cf. 
<figureCitation box="[276,394,1112,1139]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1846,1870]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,348,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[151,1436,345,1822]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus of Trygetus gromovi Marusik, 2011 (A–D), T. susianus Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021 (E), T. cyrus sp. n. (F) and T. nakhchivanicus sp. n. (G, H). A, F female, dorsal; B same, lateral; C female’s abdomen and posterior part of cephalothorax, ventral; D female’s cephalothorax, anterior; E, H male, dorsal; G same, ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683485/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
Fig. 5A– 
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, H. &amp; Jocque, R." box="[374,394,1112,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" pagination="6 - 11" refId="ref6529" refString="Ono, H. &amp; Jocque, R. (1986) Two new species of the family Zodariidae from Saudi Arabia (Arachnida: Araneae). Fauna Saudi Arabia, 8, 6 - 11." type="journal article" year="1986">H</bibRefCitation>
</figureCitation>
and Ono &amp; Jocqué 1986: fig. 5; 
<bibRefCitation author="Levy, G." box="[751,874,1113,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" pagination="67 - 110" refId="ref6399" refString="Levy, G. (1992) The spider genera Palaestina, Trygetus, Zodarion and Ranops (Araneae, Zodariidae) in Israel with annotations on species of the Middle East. Israel Journal of Zoology, 38, 67 - 110." type="journal article" year="1992">Levy 1992</bibRefCitation>
: figs 27–33, 39–41). The males described here also differ from the generotype in several characters (e.g. the shape of RTA, much shorter and not filamentous embolus, etc.). The Moroccan species (
<taxonomicName authority="Denis, 1952" authorityName="Denis" authorityYear="1952" box="[490,761,1184,1211]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berlandi">
<emphasis box="[490,614,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">T. berlandi</emphasis>
Denis, 1952
</taxonomicName>
) also appears to be misplaced in the genus, accounting the morphology of the male palp. This matter should be fully investigated in a thorough revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Jocque" authorityYear="1991" box="[1255,1351,1221,1246]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1351,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Trygetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its related genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,788,1355]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1292,1318]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,464,1293,1319]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[477,547,1293,1319]" name="Egypt" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, the Caucasus, the Middle East, south to 
<collectingCountry box="[1014,1110,1292,1318]" name="Djibouti" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
, east to 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1359,1292,1318]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="WSC" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" refId="ref6756" refString="WSC (2022) World Spider Catalog. Version 23.0. Natural History Museum Bern, Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 2 June 2022) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="url" year="2022">WSC 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
